dataIdInfo.idPurp: Humanitarian research as part of the Humane Borders OpenGIS migrant death map. These data are for internal mapping use.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
cooridors.shp obtained from Mike Kreyche on 18Feb2017 with a request to clip the southern extent of the polygons to the official US-Mexico Border. MBV and NMC used the official border file downloaded from Homeland Infrastructure Foundation-Level Data (HIFLD). Source data for the border are located here. Corridor boundaries were extended beyond the southern border and then clipped using the border line file.

Humanitarian research as part of the Humane Borders OpenGIS migrant death map. These data are for internal mapping use.
